Recommended next: pick one of the 3 remaining Rule 16 follow-up tickets — Task #21 (admin-users-list-tenant-scope) closed on 2026-05-19 as a real cross-org leak in the L6 extension, not intentional super-admin visibility. (coturn-config-fix) unblocks #14/#15/#16 e2e and is Tier 1, OR (t-slug-dev-routes-broken) unblocks #7c subdomain redirect smoke and is Tier 1. The 3rd queue item (rule-16-followup-multi-user) needs (a) coturn fixed AND (b) multi-browser rig — defer until both prereqs exist. OR pick from prior backlog: (i) BullMQ token cleanup, (d) join/[token] tRPC, (f) root landing, (binding-realtime-invalidate).

Task #21 (admin-users-list-tenant-scope) shipped on 2026-05-19:
- Tier 2 inline Opus 4.7 controller execution (no Sonnet dispatch — single coherent security fix across 11 files modified + 1 new test file, well under the 30K Sonnet budget gate but routing-decisions touch L6 extension + 7 routers + tenant-context ALS interface in one semantic change).
- ROOT CAUSE: `packages/db/src/client.ts:44` L6 tenant-guard extension had `if (!ctx || ctx.isSuperAdmin) return query(args)` bypass. Every tenant_admin who also carried `is_super_admin=true` (seeded webmaster + any future platform-staff dual-role user) silently bypassed tenant filtering on EVERY route using the guarded prisma client. security.md §SUPERADMIN AND PLATFORM-LEVEL ROLES rule 4 explicitly forbids "inline if (isSuperadmin) skip tenant filter" — and the same prohibition applies to the L6 extension itself because the extension IS the floor of every tenant-scoped resolver.
- FIX (two layers): (a) ROOT — removed `ctx.isSuperAdmin` from the bypass; only `!ctx` pass-through remains for bootstrap/seed scripts running outside `runWithTenantContext`. Rewrote client.ts header comment to document the no-bypass invariant. Dropped vestigial `isSuperAdmin: boolean` from `TenantContext` interface in `packages/db/src/tenant-context.ts` AND from the `runWithTenantContext({...})` call in `apps/web/src/server/trpc/trpc.ts:58-60`. `ctx.user.isSuperAdmin` remains on the tRPC session for RBAC role checks (`/admin/layout.tsx`, `superAdminProcedure` gate, etc.) — only the ALS-routed L6 input is removed. Verified `superadmin.ts` already uses `platformPrisma` exclusively — no callers of the removed bypass exist. (b) DEFENSE-IN-DEPTH — added explicit `where: { organization_id: ctx.organizationId }` to every list/count/aggregate query in 7 routers: admin (users.list, users.invite duplicate-check, dashboard.stats department.count + 2× user.count, reports.exportCallLogsCsv), calls (listHistory callLog.findMany), meetings (list meeting.findMany), departments (list + myBoundDepartmentIds), chat (listByMeeting chatMessage.findMany), recordings (list recording.findMany), billing (subscription.current findFirst + invoices.list findMany). Skipped `findUnique`-by-id calls — L6 handles those correctly once the bypass is removed, and adding `where: { id, organization_id }` would break Prisma's unique-constraint requirement.
- NEW `apps/web/src/server/trpc/routers/admin.test.ts` (~220 lines, 6 RED→GREEN cases) — created from scratch following the departments.test.ts mock+createCaller pattern. Tests assert (1) regular tenant_admin passes explicit organization_id in user.findMany, (2) super-admin session ALSO passes explicit organization_id (regression guard for the leak Task #21 closes), (3) explicit assertion that the where clause is neither undefined nor another org's id, (4) dashboard.stats scopes every count + findMany to caller's org_id, (5) exportCallLogsCsv scopes the CSV findMany to caller's org_id, (6) RBAC short-circuit — host role rejected with FORBIDDEN before any prisma call.
- 1 EXISTING TEST UPDATED — `departments.test.ts` myBoundDepartmentIds assertion expected single-key `where: { default_user_id }` from Phase 7 #16; updated to new defense-in-depth shape `where: { organization_id, default_user_id }`. No semantic change to the resolver behavior — purely an assertion shape catch-up.
- Validation: pnpm typecheck ✓ 0 errors 8 packages; pnpm lint ✓ 0 errors (2 pre-existing warnings unchanged); pnpm test 173/173 ✓ (167→173, +6 from new admin.test.ts); pnpm build ✓ 21 routes + middleware 141kB; pnpm audit ✓ exit 0 (HIGH = documented nodemailer per `[[nodemailer-cve-mitigation]]`).
- Two-stage review (Rule 25): Stage 1 spec PASS — security.md §SUPERADMIN AND PLATFORM-LEVEL ROLES rule 1 ("Superadmin queries that bypass tenant scoping MUST use a dedicated Prisma client instance WITHOUT the L6 tenant-guard extension") ✓ verified via grep — superadmin.ts uses platformPrisma exclusively, no callers of guarded prisma rely on bypass; rule 4 ("NEVER add an inline if (isSuperadmin) skip tenant filter") ✓ verified — removed from L6 extension at root cause. Stage 2 quality PASS — zero `any` introduced; tests written BEFORE the test-only edit to departments.test.ts (TDD: ran failing test for admin.test.ts BEFORE adding it to the suite, then GREEN); blast radius matches `git diff --stat main..HEAD` (11 mod + 1 new = 12 files, all in tRPC routers + db package + 1 test file, no unrelated changes); conventional commit message used.
- 1 new typed lesson logged: 🔴 [[l6-super-admin-bypass-leak]] documenting the pattern + the security.md §SUPERADMIN guidance + the recognition heuristic ("any phrase like 'bypass for super-admin' or 'skip tenant guard if X' inside a Prisma extension/middleware/shared helper is invisible at the call site — fix at the extension layer, not by patching every resolver").
- End state: cross-org isolation now guaranteed for every L6-guarded query regardless of caller's platform role. Super-admin cross-org access remains available via the existing `superAdminProcedure` + `platformPrisma` path (organizations.list, organizations.byId, organizations.suspend/unsuspend, platformSettings.get/update) which is explicit, gated, and logged with `PLATFORM:*` action prefix.



Phase 7 #17 — user picks from queued candidates (Socket.IO realtime foundation live since Phase 7 #8e; client-side socket-client provider + useSocket hook live since Phase 7 #10; user-level presence engine live since Phase 7 #11; department-binding presence WIRED INTO Speed Dial Board since Phase 7 #12 — green dots are live; admin self-service UI for default_user_id assignment live since Phase 7 #13 — no more pgAdmin direct edits; in-call state engine WIRED INTO Speed Dial Board since Phase 7 #14 — yellow dots are live during LiveKit calls; LEGACY SOCKET RETIRED since Phase 7 #15 — single auth-gated server now carries all socket events including call:incoming/call:rejected, [[parallel-socket-servers-coexistence]] closed; DEPT-BINDING FILTER LIVE since Phase 7 #16 — IncomingCallDialog now filters call:incoming by recipientDeptId ∈ user's boundDeptIds via new departments.myBoundDepartmentIds tRPC query + pure selectIncomingCall helper, ringing only the bound user(s) instead of every org member; RULE 16 CLEANUP SHIPPED 2026-05-19 — 6 smoke PASS + 1 PARTIAL + 5 BLOCKED, 1 env naming bug fixed inline (LIVEKIT_WS_URL → LIVEKIT_URL squash `f9f88bf`), 3 new follow-up tickets queued; nodemailer HIGH CVE mitigation locked in #9 + enforcement repaired in #10; JWT carries organizationSlug; middleware enforces URL↔session match; coverage gate live since Phase 7 #5; per-user 24h reset cap live since Phase 7 #6; TDD mandatory per Rule 25)

Rule 16 cleanup smoke pass shipped on 2026-05-19:
- Tier 2 single-session, fully inline Opus 4.7 execution (~110K context across the full pass; no Sonnet dispatch — smoke verification is inherently sequential controller work + governance writes are blast-radius-locked). Driver: Playwright MCP with system Chrome (user installed google-chrome-stable via Google's apt repo + gpg signing key — Playwright MCP defaults to /opt/google/chrome/chrome, not Playwright's bundled chromium).
- Pre-flight: prisma migrate reset --force --skip-generate (clean DB) + pnpm db:seed (webmaster — user shared WEBMASTER_PASSWORD via line-selection from CREDENTIALS.md, satisfying security.md "AI never reads CREDENTIALS.md") + /tmp/yelli-fixtures.ts tsx script (1 additional org "evil" + 4 test users in system org alice/bob/carol/david password TestPassword12345678AB bcrypt cost 12 + 1 user in evil org mallory + 3 additional departments + bindings alice→Reception, bob→Sales, david→{Front Desk, Support} multi-binding, carol→unbound). Webmaster has is_super_admin=true per seed.ts.
- PASSED 6/12: **#8e Socket.IO handshake** (curl /socket.io/?EIO=4 → HTTP 200 + sid + websocket upgrade + 25s pingInterval + CORS for :43512; browser SocketProvider connects + id verified via React fiber memoizedState introspection; WebSocket connections don't show in performance.getEntries — false-negative pitfall, must use fiber state or server logs to verify). **#10 session:invalidated** (bumping `security_version` via UPDATE SQL triggered redirect to /login in ~120s = 2× the 60s loop interval — corrects the prior smoke spec's ≤60s claim; plain sign-out alone does NOT trigger session:invalidated, only role/status/security_version changes do). **#4 forgot-password full flow** (non-enumerating message → MailHog email at :43508 → reset link → new password → login). **#11 presence multi-tab** (presence:snapshot caught with one user-id despite 2 sockets — coalescing verified; all 5 expected listeners attached; closing tab B doesn't disconnect tab A — isLast=false path works). **#12 Speed Dial green-dot** (alice signs in → Reception bound to alice goes online + clickable; bound users not signed in stay offline + disabled; React fiber confirmed useUserPresence's onlineSet contains alice's id). **#13 admin-binding-ui** (sidebar + table + dropdowns render for webmaster; non-admin alice → redirected from /admin to /app).
- PARTIAL 1/12: **#3 /app/meetings/new** — form + creation + LiveKit token mint OK after env rename fix; WebRTC peer connection fails with "could not establish pc connection" because coturn is restarting 255 (CORRECTS STATE.md's prior claim that "dev video calls work without it on localhost").
- BLOCKED 5/12: **#14 in-call yellow-dot + #15 incoming-call dialog + #16 dept-filter routing** — all need (a) 2+ distinct user sessions concurrently which Playwright MCP single-context cookie-sharing CANNOT provide AND (b) working WebRTC which coturn blocks. **#7c subdomain redirect** — /t/{slug}/* always 404 because no Next.js route handlers exist under apps/web/src/app/t/ and middleware doesn't rewrite the path.
- ONE CODE FIX SHIPPED INLINE: discovered apps/web/src/env.ts schema declared `LIVEKIT_WS_URL` but every .env.* + every compose file uses `LIVEKIT_URL` → mintLiveKitToken's wsUrl always undefined → meetings.getJoinToken returned 503 on every meeting/call. 5-line rename in env.ts (LIVEKIT_WS_URL + NEXT_PUBLIC_LIVEKIT_WS_URL → LIVEKIT_URL + NEXT_PUBLIC_LIVEKIT_URL across serverSchema + clientSchema + getServerEnv + getClientEnv) + 1-line in lib/livekit/client.ts (env.LIVEKIT_WS_URL → env.LIVEKIT_URL). Branch `fix/livekit-url-env-rename` commit `417ed97`. Validation: pnpm test 167/167 ✓ unchanged, typecheck/lint/build all green. Two-stage review (Rule 25) PASS. Squash-merged to main as `f9f88bf`.
- THREE FINDINGS QUEUED AS SEPARATE TICKETS: **(t-slug-dev-routes-broken)** — middleware extracts slug correctly but no route handlers under apps/web/src/app/t/ + no path rewrite → always 404; fix via either route handlers OR middleware rewrite (rewrite preferred — single source of truth). **(admin-users-list-tenant-scope)** — Mallory (evil org) appears in admin.users.list dropdown when current user is_super_admin=true; per security.md §SUPERADMIN forbids inline if (isSuperadmin) skip bypass — needs verification with plain tenant_admin to confirm whether it's intentional super-admin visibility or a leak. **(coturn-config-fix)** — fill COTURN_STATIC_AUTH_SECRET ⏳ placeholder in CREDENTIALS.md so coturn stops restarting + WebRTC works locally; blocks all in-call manual smoke.
- TWO OBSERVATIONS noted but not blocking: (a) login form silently fails when workspace field required and missing (no error toast — UX 🟡 polish ticket worth opening if real complaints surface); (b) SocketProvider initial-mount race may lose first presence:snapshot but state catches up via subsequent broadcasts (not consistently reproducible — worth a follow-up if real complaints surface).
- 3 new typed lessons logged: 🔴 [[livekit-env-name-mismatch]] (cross-file identifier rename discipline + Rule 16 follow-up smoke procedure for latent 503s), 🔴 [[t-slug-dev-routes-broken]] (middleware unit tests passing don't prove the constructed URL actually serves a page), 🟤 [[rule-16-cleanup-2026-05-19]] (locks Playwright MCP single-context multi-user limitation as framework decision + next-rig improvements options a/b/c).

Phase 7 #16 (department-binding-filter) shipped on 2026-05-19:
- Tier 1 single-session, fully inline Opus 4.7 execution (no Sonnet dispatch — Tier 1 score 20.5, 5 files / 138 net insertions / 7 RED→GREEN didn't justify per-task subagent overhead). User picked (department-binding-filter) from the recommended-next slot after #15. Two governance commits on main before execution: `a74f8fd` design spec (100 lines, 8 locked decisions) + `68f5a45` implementation plan (319 lines, 7-task TDD breakdown). Three branch commits before squash: `5d62cb6` T1 helper, `5a7d481` T2 query, `4ecfb04` T3 dialog. Squash SHA: `fdfc3ca`.
- NEW `apps/web/src/lib/calls/select-incoming-call.ts` (22 lines) — pure helper `selectIncomingCall(payload, boundDeptIds): boolean` per [[pure-helper-extraction-pattern]]. Returns false on `undefined` (query loading) and `[]` (user has no binding) — both treated as "do not ring" per design decisions 3+4. Uses `Array.prototype.includes` for the membership test because `Department.default_user_id` has no `@unique` constraint (decision 2 — one user may man multiple departments). Node-testable; no React imports.
- NEW `apps/web/src/lib/calls/select-incoming-call.test.ts` (35 lines, 4 RED→GREEN) — undefined → false / [] → false / mismatch (["dept-a"] vs "dept-b") → false / multi-binding match (["dept-a", "dept-c"] vs "dept-c") → true.
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/server/trpc/routers/departments.ts` (+18 lines) — new `myBoundDepartmentIds: protectedProcedure.query` placed between `list` and `create` (read-grouping). `findMany({where: {default_user_id: ctx.userId}, select: {id: true}})` then `rows.map(r => r.id)`. L6 scopes to org via runWithTenantContext (transparent). No L5 AuditLog — read-only.
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/server/trpc/routers/departments.test.ts` (+47 lines, 3 RED→GREEN) — empty result → [] / multi-binding → all matching ids in order / exact `findMany({where: {default_user_id: ctx.userId}, select: {id: true}})` shape + `expect(writeAuditLog).not.toHaveBeenCalled()`. Required extending the existing `prisma.department` mock factory with `findMany: vi.fn()` + adding it to the `$transaction` pass-through tx; audit-log test moved into its own describe block during T2 cleanup.
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/components/call/incoming-call-dialog.tsx` (+16/-6) — imports `trpc` from `@/lib/trpc/react` (path locked by T3.a grep of neighbor `department-user-picker.tsx`) and `selectIncomingCall` from `@/lib/calls/select-incoming-call`. Adds `const { data: boundDeptIds } = trpc.departments.myBoundDepartmentIds.useQuery()` near existing useState declarations. `handleIncoming` now short-circuits on `!selectIncomingCall(incoming, boundDeptIds)` before any state update / ringtone. `useEffect` dep array now `[socket, boundDeptIds, startRingtone, stopRingtone]` so listener re-binds when query resolves. Drops Phase 7 #15 TODO block.
- 7 new RED→GREEN cases (test suite 160→167). pnpm typecheck ✓ 0 errors 8 packages. pnpm lint ✓ 0 errors (2 pre-existing warnings unchanged). pnpm build ✓ 21 routes + middleware 141kB (MANDATORY per [[instrumentation-edge-stub-required]] — departments.ts in tRPC bundle transitively imported by Edge middleware). pnpm audit --audit-level=critical ✓ exit 0 (1 HIGH = documented nodemailer per [[nodemailer-cve-mitigation]]).
- Two-stage review (Rule 25): Stage 1 spec PASS (8/8 — tRPC query exists not session-encoded / `string[]` return with multi-binding test / `[]` → false / `undefined` → false / pure helper extracted / no audit log on read query / no socket type changes (lib/socket/types.ts not in diff) / no invalidate wiring (useQuery default only)); Stage 2 quality PASS (6/6 — zero `any` in new code verified via grep / only `as never` test-mock casts per established Phase 7 #13/#14/#15 pattern / TDD RED→GREEN evidenced in T1.a + T2.a terminal output / 5-file blast radius matches spec inventory exactly via `git diff --stat main..HEAD` / conventional commits on all 3 task commits / useEffect deps correct).
- 0 new typed lessons logged — patterns covered by existing entries ([[pure-helper-extraction-pattern]] for the filter helper, [[trpc-test-pattern]] for the router test additions). The schema-correctness catch during plan-phase (no `@unique` on `Department.default_user_id` → return `string[]` not single id) is captured as design decision 2 in the spec doc rather than as a typed lesson — it's a one-time schema observation, not a recurring pattern. Closes the only deferred-scope item from Phase 7 #15.
- End-to-end flow now correct: caller initiates → `calls.initiate` emits via `emitToOrg` on `${orgId}:call:incoming` with `recipientDeptId` payload field → all org sockets receive the broadcast (cross-org isolation guarded by `joinOrgChannel` since Phase 7 #15) → only the bound user's IncomingCallDialog passes the `selectIncomingCall` filter → only that user rings. Per-dept isolation now guarded client-side via the helper + tRPC query.

Phase 7 #15 (legacy-socket-retirement) shipped on 2026-05-19:
- Tier 2 subagent-driven execution (Opus 4.7 controller + Sonnet implementers/reviewers per task). Two thrash recoveries: Task 5 (router rewire + reject deletion + test creation) and Task 12 (governance docs across 2217 lines) — controller absorbed both inline after the Sonnet 30K-budget breach. User picked (legacy-socket-retirement) from recommended-next slot after #14.
- NEW `apps/web/src/server/socket/calls.ts` (53 lines) — `attachCallHandlers({io, socket})` joins `${orgId}:call:incoming` + `${orgId}:call:rejected` via `joinOrgChannel` on connect, listens for client-emitted `call:reject` events with server-resolved caller identity (reads `socket.data.session.userId`), broadcasts `call:rejected {callId, reason: "declined"}` org-scoped via `emitToOrg`. NO ROSTER — calls are ephemeral per-event transmissions unlike Phase 7 #11/#14 presence + in-call engines. Server-fixed `reason: "declined"`; `"unavailable"` reserved for future auto-timeout flows.
- NEW `apps/web/src/server/socket/calls.test.ts` (122 lines, 8 RED→GREEN) — session-guard no-op when `socket.data.session` undefined; both channels joined on connect; valid relay; 5 malformed-payload rejects (non-object, missing callId, non-string callId, empty-string callId, callId.length > 128). Hand-rolled MinimalSocket + IOServer fakes per [[socket-revalidation-test-pattern]].
- NEW `apps/web/src/lib/calls/incoming-call-handler.ts` (43 lines) — pure helper `attachIncomingCallHandler(socket, callbacks)` mirroring `lib/presence/in-call-handler.ts` byte-for-byte. Exports `MinimalIncomingCallSocketTarget` + `RejectedPayload` + `IncomingCallCallbacks` + `IncomingCallDisposer` types. Node-testable per [[pure-helper-extraction-pattern]].
- NEW `apps/web/src/lib/calls/incoming-call-handler.test.ts` (107 lines, 5 RED→GREEN) — register both listeners, onIncoming fires, onRejected fires (declined), disposer unwires + no-callbacks-after-dispose, onRejected fires (unavailable union member).
- NEW `apps/web/src/server/trpc/routers/calls.test.ts` (156 lines, 3 RED→GREEN) — happy path: emit via `emitToOrg` with org-scoped channel + recipientDeptId in payload; department not found → NOT_FOUND, no emit; `getIO()` returns null → returns connection details, no emit (graceful degradation for build/test contexts). Created from scratch — file did not exist before.
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/server/socket/server.ts` (+17 lines) — module-level `let ioInstance: IOServer | null = null` + `export function getIO()` accessor + idempotent guard `if (ioInstance !== null) return ioInstance` at top of `createSocketServer` (HMR safety mirroring legacy `initSocketServer` behavior) + `ioInstance = io` after `new IOServer(...)` + `attachCallHandlers({io, socket})` in `io.on("connection")` alongside presence + in-call.
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/server/trpc/routers/calls.ts` (-25 net) — switched import from `@/lib/socket/server` (dead) to `@/server/socket/server` + `@/server/socket/channels`; inlined `emitToOrg(io, ctx.organizationId, "call:incoming", {callId, callerName, callerDepartment, roomName, recipientDeptId})` replacing legacy `emitIncomingCall` call; DELETED entire `reject` mutation (was lines 81-98, ~18 lines) — zero call sites; rejection now flows through `socket.emit("call:reject")` in the dialog.
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/lib/livekit/types.ts` (+1 line) — added `recipientDeptId: string` field to `IncomingCallPayload` for future client-side dept filter (TODO follow-up in #16).
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/lib/socket/types.ts` (-17 lines) — deleted `presence:subscribe` + `presence:heartbeat` + `presence:update` events (orphaned by Phase 7 #11/#12 migration + legacy server deletion); deleted `subscribedDepartmentIds: Set<string>` field on `SocketData`; deleted `callIncomingRoom` + `callerRoom` helper exports; deleted `PresenceState` import (only used by deleted `presence:update`).
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/components/call/incoming-call-dialog.tsx` (-55+30 net) — drop `import { io, type Socket } from "socket.io-client"`; drop `SOCKET_URL` constant + `socketRef` ref; switch to `useSocketOptional()` for shared socket reference + `attachIncomingCallHandler(socket, {onIncoming, onRejected})` for listener wiring. Now subscribes to BOTH `call:incoming` AND `call:rejected` (former was the only event handled by raw io() before, but raw io() was hitting a 503 placeholder so neither actually worked end-to-end). Reject button emits via shared socket: `socket?.emit("call:reject", {callId: payload.callId})`. TODO follow-up (Phase 7 #16 candidate): filter onIncoming by `incoming.recipientDeptId === currentUser.boundDeptId`.
- DELETED `apps/web/src/lib/socket/server.ts` (159 lines) — `initSocketServer()` had ZERO call sites in `apps/web/src`. Phantom `server/custom-server.ts` referenced in module comments never existed (abandoned at Phase 7 #8e-1 in favor of separate-SOCKET_PORT pattern via `instrumentation.ts`). `getIO()` always returned null in production — incoming-call had been broken end-to-end since the architectural pivot. Phase 7 #15 was the FIRST real implementation, not a migration.
- DELETED `apps/web/src/app/api/socket/route.ts` (39 lines) — Next.js Route Handler that returned 503; intentional placeholder for the abandoned `server/custom-server.ts` path. Route Handlers cannot perform WebSocket upgrades anyway. The raw `io()` connection from `incoming-call-dialog` had been hitting this 503 since Phase 7 #8e-1.
- 16 new RED→GREEN cases (test suite 144→160). pnpm typecheck ✓ 0 errors 8 packages. pnpm lint ✓ 0 errors (2 pre-existing warnings unchanged). pnpm build ✓ 22 routes + middleware 141kB compiled in ~51s (MANDATORY per [[instrumentation-edge-stub-required]] — calls.ts joins createSocketServer import chain). pnpm audit --audit-level=critical ✓ exit 0 (Phase 7 #9 + #10 still in effect; 1 HIGH = documented nodemailer per [[nodemailer-cve-mitigation]]).
- Two-stage review (Rule 25): Stage 1 spec PASS (10/10 — attachCallHandlers exists with locked signature, wired in connection block, getIO singleton + idempotent guard, calls.initiate imports from new paths, emit includes recipientDeptId, reject mutation deleted, both legacy files removed, types cleanup verified by grep, dialog uses useSocketOptional + attachIncomingCallHandler, reject button via shared socket); Stage 2 quality PASS (8/8 — zero any, no unjustified assertions, TDD RED→GREEN, blast-radius only, conventional commits, event-name consistency across 4 files, disposer mirrors precedent, Edge-build green).
- 0 new typed lessons logged — existing patterns covered everything ([[pure-helper-extraction-pattern]], [[socket-revalidation-test-pattern]], [[event-handler-disposer-test-pattern]], [[instrumentation-edge-stub-required]], [[nodemailer-cve-mitigation]]). New process observation worth noting (not encoded as typed lesson yet): Sonnet subagents thrash on multi-file integration tasks (Task 5 router rewire) and on governance-file edits spanning 2000+ lines (Task 12). Future tickets with similar shape should either pre-bake context aggressively (one bash with all relevant file excerpts in one tool call) or stay inline. Reviewer subagents stayed within budget throughout.
