(rule-16-cleanup) Visual QA debt batch — RECOMMENDED NEXT
    Four realtime engines now wired into UI: Phase 7 #11 user-level presence, #12 dept binding
    presence (green dots), #14 in-call (yellow dots), #15+#16 incoming-call dialog with dept
    filter. The accumulated browser-smoke debt is worth clearing in one sitting now that the
    end-to-end happy path is correct. New for #16: bind tab A's user to dept-X and tab B's user
    to dept-Y via /admin/departments, then tab A calls dept-Y via Speed Dial → ONLY tab B's
    dialog rings (tab A should NOT ring itself; any third tab whose user is bound to a different
    dept stays silent). Plus all carried-over smoke tests for #3 (/app/meetings/new), #4
    (/forgot-password + /reset-password), #7c (subdomain redirect), #8e+#10 (Socket.IO handshake
    + session:invalidated), #11 (presence engine), #12 (Speed Dial green-dot), #13 (admin
    binding UI), #14 (in-call yellow-dot), #15 (incoming-call dialog end-to-end).

(binding-realtime-invalidate) Real-time bound-dept cache invalidation
    Phase 7 #16 design decision 8 deferred this explicitly. Currently when an admin re-binds a
    user → dept mapping via /admin/departments while that user has the IncomingCallDialog
    mounted, the open dialog only picks up the new boundDeptIds on next window-focus (default
    useQuery refetch-on-focus). For perfect sync: emit `binding:changed {userId}` from the
    setDefaultUser mutation → server fans out org-scoped to that user's open sockets → client
    invalidates the `myBoundDepartmentIds` query immediately. Defer further unless real
    complaints surface in production. Tier 1 (small surface — 1 server event + 1 mutation hook
    + 1 client invalidator).

(i) Periodic cleanup of expired/consumed password_reset_tokens
    BullMQ scheduled job to DELETE consumed tokens > 30 days old and unconsumed expired tokens > 7 days. Keeps the table from
    growing unboundedly. Pairs naturally with #6: the cap-met silent-skip and the cleanup job together close the token-table
    lifecycle. The count query introduced in #6 stays fast forever if the cleanup runs daily.
    Tier 2 (BullMQ worker + scheduler + tests + deploy config).

(d) join/[token] tRPC                          [needs LiveKit ⏳ for full integration]
    Unit tests OK against mocked LiveKit token mint; integration deferred until LIVEKIT_API_KEY filled.
    Existing getJoinToken in meetingsRouter has 0 test coverage — could pair with this if scope allows.

(f) Root landing page                          [verify scope first]
    Current /page.tsx is 11 lines — check PRODUCT.md for what's expected. Likely Tier 1.

(rule-16-cleanup) Visual QA debt batch          [pairs naturally with department-binding-filter — recommended companion]
    Now that build is green again on `main`, clear accumulated smoke tests:
    - /forgot-password + /reset-password (Phase 7 #4 carryover)
    - /app/meetings/new (#3 carryover)
    - subdomain redirect (#7c carryover) — `acme.localhost` / `evil.localhost` in /etc/hosts OR /t/{slug} path pattern
    - Socket.IO handshake (Phase 7 #8e carryover) — `curl http://localhost:43515/socket.io/` returns handshake page + browser
      session in /app connects to ws://localhost:43515
    - Socket.IO session:invalidated trigger (Phase 7 #10) — open a tab in /app, trigger session invalidation in another tab
      (sign out OR admin disables user), wait ≤60s, verify connected socket receives `session:invalidated` event AND the tab
      redirects to /login automatically.
    - NEW: Presence engine smoke (Phase 7 #11) — open two browser tabs (same user), verify the snapshot includes self AND
      another peer in the same org. Sign out / close one tab — verify other tab does NOT see user go offline (multi-tab
      coalescing held). Close the last tab — verify peers in the org receive `presence:user {online:false}` within transport
      timeout (~25s pingInterval + 20s pingTimeout = ~45s worst-case).
    - NEW: Speed Dial green-dot smoke (Phase 7 #12) — open pgAdmin, bind one demo department's `default_user_id` to the
      webmaster user id (UPDATE departments SET default_user_id = '<webmaster-id>' WHERE name = 'Reception'). Sign in as
      webmaster in /app → wait for socket handshake (~1s) → verify the Reception speed-dial button shows a green dot AND is
      clickable (not disabled). Sign out → wait for transport timeout (~45s) → verify the dot returns to gray AND the button
      becomes disabled. Verify an unbound department (default_user_id IS NULL) stays gray + disabled throughout (matches
      existing offline UX).

