Rule 25 reminder for ALL of the above:
  → Write failing test FIRST (RED), then implementation (GREEN), then refactor.
  → Test patterns:
      [[trpc-test-pattern]] (Phase 7 #2)
      [[meetings-protected-route-test]] (Phase 7 #3)
      [[trpc-test-with-env-mock]] (Phase 7 #4)
      [[direct-callback-test-pattern]] (Phase 7 #7c-1 — exercises authConfig.callbacks directly)
      [[pure-helper-extraction-pattern]] (Phase 7 #7c-2 / #8e / #10 / #11 — extract Edge-incompatible or React-incompatible code into separate file for Node test runner)
      [[socket-auth-test-pattern]] (Phase 7 #8e-1 — mock next-auth/jwt decode + assert decode receives correct salt)
      [[socket-revalidation-test-pattern]] (Phase 7 #8e-2 — mock io.fetchSockets + prisma.user.findMany; assert disconnect/emit per stale-session branch)
      [[socket-client-factory-test-pattern]] (Phase 7 #10 — vi.mock("socket.io-client"); assert io() receives correct URL + opts)
      [[event-handler-disposer-test-pattern]] (Phase 7 #10 — hand-rolled MinimalSocket fake; assert register/fire/dispose/no-cross-fire)
      [[presence-roster-coalesce-pattern]] (Phase 7 #11 — Map<orgId, Map<userId, Set<socketId>>> with {wasFirst}/{isLast} semantics; mock io.to(...).emit(...) per [[socket-revalidation-test-pattern]] precedent)
      [[pure-helper-extraction-pattern]] (Phase 7 #7c-2 / #8e / #10 / #11 / #12 — extract React-incompatible OR Edge-incompatible OR simply node-testable logic into a separate file; the React component becomes a thin composition that's correct-by-construction)
  → For forms: reuse the [[shadcn-form-primitive]] pattern from Phase 7 #3.
  → For shared schemas: `<Entity>CreateClientInputSchema` for client-facing input, `<Entity>CreateInputSchema` for admin/internal projection.
  → For new env vars consumed by routers: add `vi.mock("@/env", ...)` to the test file.
  → For new JWT fields: wire BOTH session callbacks (auth.config.ts Edge-safe AND auth.ts DB-revalidating) — see [[edge-safe-vs-db-revalidating-callback-duplication]].
  → For new Auth.js v5 decode contexts (anywhere outside Next.js itself): pass the COOKIE NAME as the `salt` parameter — see [[authjs-v5-jwe-cookie-salt]].
  → For new Socket.IO room subscriptions: use the org-scoped helper pattern (`joinOrgChannel(socket, eventType)` with no org-id parameter) — see [[socket-cross-org-api-surface-guard]].
  → For new Socket.IO client events emitted from React: consume via `useSocket()` from `@/lib/socket/socket-context` — do NOT instantiate `io()` directly.
  → For new realtime broadcast features (org-scoped fan-out): follow the `emitToOrg(io, organizationId, eventType, payload)` pattern; never accept an orgId parameter on the subscription path (sourced from session only).
  → For multi-tab presence/notification engines: use the `{wasFirst}`/`{isLast}` roster coalescing pattern from Phase 7 #11 to avoid flicker on tab refresh / HMR / reconnect.
  → For new events added to lib/socket/types.ts: use DISTINCT event names from any legacy event (the legacy /api/socket server still consumes the same type map — see [[parallel-socket-servers-coexistence]]).
  → When a router becomes fully tested (>95% across all four metrics), add a per-file threshold to apps/web/vitest.config.ts — see [[vitest-per-file-glob-thresholds]].
  → Coverage thresholds rise organically — add tests → measure → bump threshold. Do NOT lower thresholds to make a regression "fix" pass.
  → NEW (Phase 7 #6): for any new throttle/cap design on auth flows, follow [[per-user-24h-cap-pattern]].
  → NEW (Phase 7 #7c): for any work that touches CLAUDE.md / .claude/rules/* / governance docs, prefer Opus-executor over Sonnet dispatch — Sonnet subagents thrash on SessionStart hooks. See [[sonnet-thrash-sessionstart-hooks]].
  → NEW (Phase 7 #7c): for any middleware.ts edit, IGNORE the vercel-plugin nextjs auto-suggestion to rename to proxy.ts — Yelli is on Next.js 15.5.18. See [[proxy-ts-false-positive]].
  → NEW (Phase 7 #9): for unfixed HIGH CVEs in transitively-pinned deps, follow the 5-step decision tree in [[nodemailer-cve-mitigation]] — trace exploit reachability, JSDoc the call site, DECISIONS_LOG entry with revisit triggers, `.npmrc audit-level=critical`, AND a matching `--audit-level=critical` CLI flag in CI (per #10 correction).
  → NEW (Phase 7 #10): for any work touching `apps/web/src/instrumentation.ts` or its transitively-imported modules, MUST run `pnpm build` as part of validation per [[instrumentation-edge-stub-required]]. test/typecheck/lint are not sufficient to catch Edge-bundle webpack failures.
  → NEW (Phase 7 #10): for any audit policy claim, run `pnpm audit` BARE (no flag) and verify exit code — `.npmrc audit-level` does NOT control the bare exit code on pnpm 10. See [[pnpm10-audit-level-ignored]].
  → NEW (Phase 7 #11): test fakes that need to satisfy overloaded interfaces (per-event-name payload typing) use a `loose as unknown as Interface` boundary cast — established precedent `} as never` (revalidation.test.ts) and `as unknown as IOServer` (channels.test.ts). Keeps production typing strict while letting test runtime be loose.

Recommended next: (rule-16-cleanup) — with Phase 7 #16 shipping the dept filter on the IncomingCallDialog (end-to-end happy path now correct), the accumulated visual-QA debt is worth burning through in one sitting. Four realtime engines are live across the UI surface (Phase 7 #11 user-level presence, #12 dept binding presence, #14 in-call yellow dots, #15+#16 incoming-call dialog with dept filter) — smoke them all in one browser session. OR (binding-realtime-invalidate) if perfect-sync on admin re-bind matters (Phase 7 #16 decision 8 explicitly deferred this; default useQuery refetch-on-focus is good enough for most cases). OR (i) BullMQ cleanup as clean Tier 2 housekeeping. Save (d) join/[token] for when LIVEKIT_API_KEY is filled. (f) root landing is a tiny fill-in if you want to clear the smallest open ticket first.

